The workers at Blue Bird in Fort Valley, Georgia, have voted to unionize and join the United Steelworkers. They are praised for building electric school buses that contribute to America's clean energy future and improve air quality for children. The article emphasizes the importance of unions in building the middle class and creating good-paying jobs that can support families. It also challenges the notion that America cannot lead in manufacturing again, highlighting the workers at Blue Bird and similar companies as examples of the future being built in America, with unions playing a significant role.